<br>
FoH is probably the best guild across servers so there is no telling how many mobs they are able to clear in a 5 hour span to get 10 drops. I think that is the point being overlooked. Yes you know you will get spells because you are in a uber guild ect...I really don't believe everyone should have to go through this crap. Ubers need to understand that you can be a hard-core gamer (i.e. experience and spend 8+ hours a day online), and not be in a min/max guild.<br>
<br>
I don't feel I should have to join one of the top 3 guilds on my server to get spells that balance the class. Ancient spells should be rare and caster loot. Normally spells should be accessible to all casters with some effort. 12hours per parchment drop is insane for a 6 man group of level 61 to 62 players. Casters improve by loot as well however our spells are mainstays. We shouldn't be double penalized. I mean you can't possibly think that two mages with complete spell books are equal if one is wearing top-end Luclin gear and the other is in a tola rob. I know for a fact that i am more powerful with my BoBC then a mage without them. Loot is very important and mages seem to benefit the most from loot more then any caster class. No class should be double penalized like this.<br>
<br>
Also I have put in 2 1/2 years in EQ. I have two level 60 epic characters, and consider myself a &quot;hard-core&quot; player. Just because I choose not to be in a min/max guild doesn't mean I should have basic spells that balance the class held from me. Ancient Spells and Loot should seperate you and me, not the fact that I have 4 or 5 spells in my spell book due to nothing more then a insane time sink made to benefit the uber. I also feel that I am just as important as the cleric next to me. I have invested alot of time in EQ, and to be pushed aside to allow &quot;loved classes&quot; to have first dibbs over me would not go over well. It is those reasons why I am not in a uber guild.<br>
<br>
I spent 35 hours killing named mobs and white/yellow cons and saw two parchment drop. I got one and turned it in and got fire bolt of tallon. I am sorry but spending over 35 hours experience since release makes me a hard core gamer and to have only the store purchased spell is crap.  I know a great number of non-guilded folk that play there class at a high level. I am willing to bet some would make alot of ubers look silly.  This is a game and the basic workings like spells ect..should be accessible to all with some work. This is like the mage epic revisited.<br>
